goals.visualization: scatter plot of income vs health
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand if there is a correlation between income and health. We can see if countries with higher income also have better health outcomes.

goals.question: What is the distribution of population across regions?
goals.visualization: bar chart of population by region
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the population distribution across different regions. We can see which regions have the highest and lowest populations.

goals.question: What is the average income per person in each region?
goals.visualization: box plot of income by region

goals.question: What is the distribution of health index across regions?
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the health distribution across different regions. We can see which regions have the highest and lowest health index.

goals.question: What is the relationship between income and population?

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='income', y='health')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the relationship between income and health?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
